{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is at module handoff (summary-write path must query stored per-dimension findings for the same round), not just one pure function. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess is required; an in-process repository/DB is enough. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection-gate: System is disqualified by behavior text 'stored ... for the same round' (data consistency check), not real infrastructure; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because this behavior is about gating on stored verdicts, not model output quality.","test_description":"Wire review-summary service + findings repository + round context store (in-process DB). Seed one round with at least one FAIL dimension finding, then attempt to persist PASS summary. Assert write is rejected with a domain error and persisted summary remains non-PASS/unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: real failure appears when gate logic + storage reader + summary text coexist; unit-testing only a compute function can miss wrong data source selection. REAL-INFRA: no required real HTTP/OS/subprocess. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection-gate: higher levels are disqualified because behavior explicitly contrasts data sources ('reads ... stored findings directly' vs 'summary text'), which is module wiring/data-source precedence, not external infra or model behavior.","test_description":"Construct a round where stored findings include FAIL but summary text says all PASS. Run stop-gate verdict computation through the real service/repo wiring. Assert final verdict is FAIL/BLOCKED and that changing summary text alone cannot flip outcome.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.77,"System":0.015,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: behavior spans request handling, authorization/flag enforcement, and audit persistence. A single-function unit test would miss missing audit writes or bypass paths. REAL-INFRA: can be caught with in-process modules and local DB; no mandatory external infra. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Rejection-gate: System is disqualified because 'explicit override flag' and 'auditable warning record' can be validated with local persistence; no real OS/network dependency in behavior text.","test_description":"Run summary-finalization API/service with two cases: (1) override text without override flag -> rejected; (2) with override flag -> accepted but emits/persists warning audit record containing actor, round, reason, and timestamp. Verify audit record exists in store.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is orchestration/state linkage across fix phase, diff versioning, and review-round freshness checks. REAL-INFRA: no requirement for real subprocess/network if diff/version and review-run metadata are represented in-process. LLM-DEP: correctness here is about requiring a new round to exist, not judging model output quality. MULTI-STEP: sequence exists, but not multiple real agentic quality-dependent steps, so Workflow is not minimum. Rejection-gate: Agentic/Workflow are disqualified by behavior text 'cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh ... round is executed' (process guard), not 'agent must produce correct judgment'.","test_description":"Model two diff revisions: pre-fix and post-fix. Seed latest findings only for pre-fix round, then attempt PASS finalize after Phase 4 update; assert blocked due to stale round. Add a new review-round record tied to updated diff and passing findings; assert finalize can proceed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.76,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: requires interaction of round-counter policy, findings severity state, and final outcome emitter. Unit-only tests can miss policy wiring bugs. REAL-INFRA: no mandatory real OS/network/subprocess. LLM-DEP: outcome depends on stored MUST-FIX presence, not stochastic model quality. MULTI-STEP: sequential rounds exist, but can be simulated deterministically without full agent pipeline. Rejection-gate: System/Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because behavior text is policy outcome ('rounds exhausted' + 'unresolved MUST-FIX') over stored state.","test_description":"Configure max rounds N. Seed unresolved MUST-FIX findings through round N without resolution. Execute finalization path and assert emitted terminal outcome is ESCALATION (with reason/context), and PASS is unreachable in this state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.015,"Workflow":0.015}}]}
